FBIS4-15028 "drsov066_b_94029" FBIS-SOV-94-066 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Ministry Forecasts Reduced Coal Mining Ministry Forecasts Reduced Coal Mining LD0504134294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1214 GMT 5 Apr 94 LD0504134294 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Text] Moscow April 5 BUSINESS-TASS -- Russia is going to reduce the output of coal by 20 to 35 million tonnes in 1994 to 275 million tonnes, according to the Economy Ministry's forecast. One of the main problems facing the sector, according to experts from the Economy Ministry, is the continuing deterioration of the production assets in the mines, which increases the cost and the risk of mining.
